2891 void MacroAssembler::MulS32(Register dst, const MemOperand& src1) {
2892  if (is_uint12(src1.offset())) {
2893  ms(dst, src1);
2894  } else if (is_int20(src1.offset())) {
2895  msy(dst, src1);
2896  } else {
2897  UNIMPLEMENTED();
2898  }
2899 }

3147 void MacroAssembler::MulHighS64(Register dst, Register src1, Register src2) {
3148  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(MISC_INSTR_EXT2)) {
3149  mgrk(r0, src1, src2);
3150  lgr(dst, r0);
3151  } else {
3152  SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode = SaveFPRegsMode::kSave;
3153  PushCallerSaved(fp_mode, ip);
3154  Push(src1, src2);
3155  Pop(r2, r3);
3156  {
3157  FrameScope scope(this, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
3158  PrepareCallCFunction(2, 0, r0);
3159  CallCFunction(ExternalReference::int64_mul_high_function(), 2, 0);
3160  }
3161  mov(r0, r2);
3162  PopCallerSaved(fp_mode, ip);
3163  mov(dst, r0);
3164  }
3165 }

3438 // Subtract 32-bit (Register = Register - Register)
3439 void MacroAssembler::SubS32(Register dst, Register src1, Register src2) {
3440  // Use non-clobbering version if possible
3441  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
3442  srk(dst, src1, src2);
3443  return;
3444  }
3445  if (dst != src1 && dst != src2) lr(dst, src1);
3446  // In scenario where we have dst = src - dst, we need to swap and negate
3447  if (dst != src1 && dst == src2) {
3448  Label done;
3449  lcr(dst, dst); // dst = -dst
3450  b(overflow, &done);
3451  ar(dst, src1); // dst = dst + src
3452  bind(&done);
3453  } else {
3454  sr(dst, src2);
3455  }
3456 }
3457 
3458 // Subtract Pointer Sized (Register = Register - Register)
3459 void MacroAssembler::SubS64(Register dst, Register src1, Register src2) {
3460  // Use non-clobbering version if possible
3461  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
3462  sgrk(dst, src1, src2);
3463  return;
3464  }
3465  if (dst != src1 && dst != src2) mov(dst, src1);
3466  // In scenario where we have dst = src - dst, we need to swap and negate
3467  if (dst != src1 && dst == src2) {
3468  Label done;
3469  lcgr(dst, dst); // dst = -dst
3470  b(overflow, &done);
3471  AddS64(dst, src1); // dst = dst + src
3472  bind(&done);
3473  } else {
3474  SubS64(dst, src2);
3475  }
3476 }

3544 // Non-clobbering AND 32-bit - dst = src1 & src1
3545 void MacroAssembler::And(Register dst, Register src1, Register src2) {
3546  if (dst != src1 && dst != src2) {
3547  // We prefer to generate XR/XGR, over the non clobbering XRK/XRK
3548  // as XR is a smaller instruction
3549  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
3550  nrk(dst, src1, src2);
3551  return;
3552  } else {
3553  lr(dst, src1);
3554  }
3555  } else if (dst == src2) {
3556  src2 = src1;
3557  }
3558  And(dst, src2);
3559 }

3564  // We prefer to generate XR/XGR, over the non clobbering XRK/XRK
3565  // as XR is a smaller instruction
3566  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
3567  ngrk(dst, src1, src2);
3568  return;
3569  } else {
3570  mov(dst, src1);
3571  }
3572  } else if (dst == src2) {

3596 // AND Pointer Size - dst = dst & imm
3597 void MacroAssembler::AndP(Register dst, const Operand& opnd) {
3598  intptr_t value = opnd.immediate();
3599  if (value >> 32 != -1) {
3600  // this may not work b/c condition code won't be set correctly
3601  nihf(dst, Operand(value >> 32));
3602  }
3603  nilf(dst, Operand(value & 0xFFFFFFFF));
3604 }
3605 
3606 // AND 32-bit - dst = src & imm
3607 void MacroAssembler::And(Register dst, Register src, const Operand& opnd) {
3608  if (dst != src) lr(dst, src);
3609  nilf(dst, opnd);
3610 }
3611 
3612 // AND Pointer Size - dst = src & imm
3613 void MacroAssembler::AndP(Register dst, Register src, const Operand& opnd) {
3614  // Try to exploit RISBG first
3615  intptr_t value = opnd.immediate();
3616  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(GENERAL_INSTR_EXT)) {
3617  intptr_t shifted_value = value;
3618  int trailing_zeros = 0;
3619 
3620  // We start checking how many trailing zeros are left at the end.
3621  while ((0 != shifted_value) && (0 == (shifted_value & 1))) {
3622  trailing_zeros++;
3623  shifted_value >>= 1;
3624  }
3625 
3626  // If temp (value with right-most set of zeros shifted out) is 1 less
3627  // than power of 2, we have consecutive bits of 1.
3628  // Special case: If shift_value is zero, we cannot use RISBG, as it requires
3629  // selection of at least 1 bit.
3630  if ((0 != shifted_value) && base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(shifted_value + 1)) {
3631  int startBit =
3632  base::bits::CountLeadingZeros64(shifted_value) - trailing_zeros;
3633  int endBit = 63 - trailing_zeros;
3634  // Start: startBit, End: endBit, Shift = 0, true = zero unselected bits.
3635  RotateInsertSelectBits(dst, src, Operand(startBit), Operand(endBit),
3636  Operand::Zero(), true);
3637  return;
3638  } else if (-1 == shifted_value) {
3639  // A Special case in which all top bits up to MSB are 1's. In this case,
3640  // we can set startBit to be 0.
3641  int endBit = 63 - trailing_zeros;
3642  RotateInsertSelectBits(dst, src, Operand::Zero(), Operand(endBit),
3643  Operand::Zero(), true);
3644  return;
3645  }
3646  }
3647 
3648  // If we are &'ing zero, we can just whack the dst register and skip copy
3649  if (dst != src && (0 != value)) mov(dst, src);
3650  AndP(dst, opnd);
3651 }
3652

3656 // OR Pointer Size - dst = dst & src
3657 void MacroAssembler::OrP(Register dst, Register src) { ogr(dst, src); }
3658 
3659 // Non-clobbering OR 32-bit - dst = src1 & src1
3660 void MacroAssembler::Or(Register dst, Register src1, Register src2) {
3661  if (dst != src1 && dst != src2) {
3662  // We prefer to generate XR/XGR, over the non clobbering XRK/XRK
3663  // as XR is a smaller instruction
3664  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
3665  ork(dst, src1, src2);
3666  return;
3667  } else {
3668  lr(dst, src1);
3669  }
3670  } else if (dst == src2) {
3671  src2 = src1;
3672  }
3673  Or(dst, src2);
3674 }
3675 
3676 // Non-clobbering OR pointer size - dst = src1 & src1
3677 void MacroAssembler::OrP(Register dst, Register src1, Register src2) {
3678  if (dst != src1 && dst != src2) {
3679  // We prefer to generate XR/XGR, over the non clobbering XRK/XRK
3680  // as XR is a smaller instruction
3681  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
3682  ogrk(dst, src1, src2);
3683  return;
3684  } else {
3685  mov(dst, src1);
3686  }
3687  } else if (dst == src2) {
3688  src2 = src1;
3689  }
3690  OrP(dst, src2);
3691 }
3692 
3693 // OR 32-bit (Reg - Mem)
3694 void MacroAssembler::Or(Register dst, const MemOperand& opnd) {
3695  DCHECK(is_int20(opnd.offset()));
3696  if (is_uint12(opnd.offset()))
3697  o(dst, opnd);
3698  else
3699  oy(dst, opnd);
3700 }
3701 
3702 // OR Pointer Size (Reg - Mem)
3703 void MacroAssembler::OrP(Register dst, const MemOperand& opnd) {
3704  DCHECK(is_int20(opnd.offset()));
3705  og(dst, opnd);
3706 }
3707 
3708 // OR 32-bit - dst = dst & imm
3709 void MacroAssembler::Or(Register dst, const Operand& opnd) { oilf(dst, opnd); }
3710 
3711 // OR Pointer Size - dst = dst & imm
3712 void MacroAssembler::OrP(Register dst, const Operand& opnd) {
3713  intptr_t value = opnd.immediate();
3714  if (value >> 32 != 0) {
3715  // this may not work b/c condition code won't be set correctly
3716  oihf(dst, Operand(value >> 32));
3717  }
3718  oilf(dst, Operand(value & 0xFFFFFFFF));
3719 }
3720 
3721 // OR 32-bit - dst = src & imm
3722 void MacroAssembler::Or(Register dst, Register src, const Operand& opnd) {
3723  if (dst != src) lr(dst, src);
3724  oilf(dst, opnd);
3725 }
3726 
3727 // OR Pointer Size - dst = src & imm
3728 void MacroAssembler::OrP(Register dst, Register src, const Operand& opnd) {
3729  if (dst != src) mov(dst, src);
3730  OrP(dst, opnd);
3731 }
3732 
3733 // XOR 32-bit - dst = dst & src
3734 void MacroAssembler::Xor(Register dst, Register src) { xr(dst, src); }
3735 
3736 // XOR Pointer Size - dst = dst & src
3737 void MacroAssembler::XorP(Register dst, Register src) { xgr(dst, src); }
3738 
3739 // Non-clobbering XOR 32-bit - dst = src1 & src1
3740 void MacroAssembler::Xor(Register dst, Register src1, Register src2) {
3741  if (dst != src1 && dst != src2) {
3742  // We prefer to generate XR/XGR, over the non clobbering XRK/XRK
3743  // as XR is a smaller instruction
3744  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
3745  xrk(dst, src1, src2);
3746  return;
3747  } else {
3748  lr(dst, src1);
3749  }
3750  } else if (dst == src2) {
3751  src2 = src1;
3752  }
3753  Xor(dst, src2);
3754 }
3755 
3756 // Non-clobbering XOR pointer size - dst = src1 & src1
3757 void MacroAssembler::XorP(Register dst, Register src1, Register src2) {
3758  if (dst != src1 && dst != src2) {
3759  // We prefer to generate XR/XGR, over the non clobbering XRK/XRK
3760  // as XR is a smaller instruction
3761  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
3762  xgrk(dst, src1, src2);
3763  return;
3764  } else {
3765  mov(dst, src1);
3766  }
3767  } else if (dst == src2) {
3768  src2 = src1;
3769  }
3770  XorP(dst, src2);
3771 }
3772 
3773 // XOR 32-bit (Reg - Mem)
3774 void MacroAssembler::Xor(Register dst, const MemOperand& opnd) {
3775  DCHECK(is_int20(opnd.offset()));
3776  if (is_uint12(opnd.offset()))
3777  x(dst, opnd);
3778  else
3779  xy(dst, opnd);
3780 }

3782 // XOR Pointer Size (Reg - Mem)

3785  xg(dst, opnd);
3786 }

3788 // XOR 32-bit - dst = dst & imm

3790 
3791 // XOR Pointer Size - dst = dst & imm
3792 void MacroAssembler::XorP(Register dst, const Operand& opnd) {
3793  intptr_t value = opnd.immediate();
3794  xihf(dst, Operand(value >> 32));
3795  xilf(dst, Operand(value & 0xFFFFFFFF));
3796 }

3800  if (dst != src) lr(dst, src);
3801  xilf(dst, opnd);
3802 }

3838 // Compare 32-bit Register vs Register
3839 void MacroAssembler::CmpS32(Register src1, Register src2) { cr_z(src1, src2); }
3840 
3841 // Compare Pointer Sized Register vs Register
3842 void MacroAssembler::CmpS64(Register src1, Register src2) { cgr(src1, src2); }
3843 
3844 // Compare 32-bit Register vs Immediate
3845 // This helper will set up proper relocation entries if required.
3846 void MacroAssembler::CmpS32(Register dst, const Operand& opnd) {
3847  if (opnd.rmode() == RelocInfo::NO_INFO) {
3848  intptr_t value = opnd.immediate();
3849  if (is_int16(value))
3850  chi(dst, opnd);
3851  else
3852  cfi(dst, opnd);
3853  } else {
3854  // Need to generate relocation record here
3855  RecordRelocInfo(opnd.rmode(), opnd.immediate());
3856  cfi(dst, opnd);
3857  }
3858 }
3859 
3860 // Compare Pointer Sized Register vs Immediate
3861 // This helper will set up proper relocation entries if required.
3862 void MacroAssembler::CmpS64(Register dst, const Operand& opnd) {
3863  if (opnd.rmode() == RelocInfo::NO_INFO) {
3864  cgfi(dst, opnd);
3865  } else {
3866  mov(r0, opnd); // Need to generate 64-bit relocation
3867  cgr(dst, r0);
3868  }
3869 }
3870 
3871 // Compare 32-bit Register vs Memory
3872 void MacroAssembler::CmpS32(Register dst, const MemOperand& opnd) {
3873  // make sure offset is within 20 bit range
3874  DCHECK(is_int20(opnd.offset()));
3875  if (is_uint12(opnd.offset()))
3876  c(dst, opnd);
3877  else
3878  cy(dst, opnd);
3879 }
3880 
3881 // Compare Pointer Size Register vs Memory
3882 void MacroAssembler::CmpS64(Register dst, const MemOperand& opnd) {
3883  // make sure offset is within 20 bit range
3884  DCHECK(is_int20(opnd.offset()));
3885  cg(dst, opnd);
3886 }

3963  intptr_t value = opnd.immediate();

3970 // Branch On Count. Decrement R1, and branch if R1 != 0.
3971 void MacroAssembler::BranchOnCount(Register r1, Label* l) {
3972  int32_t offset = branch_offset(l);
3973  if (is_int16(offset)) {
3974  brctg(r1, Operand(offset));
3975  } else {
3976  AddS64(r1, Operand(-1));
3977  Branch(ne, Operand(offset));
3978  }
3979 }

3981 void MacroAssembler::LoadSmiLiteral(Register dst, Tagged<Smi> smi) {
3982  intptr_t value = static_cast<intptr_t>(smi.ptr());
3983 #if defined(V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS) || defined(V8_31BIT_SMIS_ON_64BIT_ARCH)
3984  llilf(dst, Operand(value));
3985 #else
3986  DCHECK_EQ(value & 0xFFFFFFFF, 0);
3987  // The smi value is loaded in upper 32-bits. Lower 32-bit are zeros.
3988  llihf(dst, Operand(value >> 32));
3989 #endif
3990 }
3991 
3992 void MacroAssembler::CmpSmiLiteral(Register src1, Tagged<Smi> smi,
3993  Register scratch) {
3994 #if defined(V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS) || defined(V8_31BIT_SMIS_ON_64BIT_ARCH)
3995  // CFI takes 32-bit immediate.
3996  cfi(src1, Operand(smi));
3997 #else
3998  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
3999  cih(src1, Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(smi.ptr()) >> 32));
4000  } else {
4001  LoadSmiLiteral(scratch, smi);
4002  cgr(src1, scratch);
4003  }
4004 #endif
4005 }

4007 void MacroAssembler::LoadU64(Register dst, const MemOperand& mem,
4008  Register scratch) {
4009  int offset = mem.offset();
4010 
4011  MemOperand src = mem;
4012  if (!is_int20(offset)) {
4013  DCHECK(scratch != no_reg && scratch != r0 && mem.rx() == r0);
4014  DCHECK(scratch != mem.rb());
4015  mov(scratch, Operand(offset));
4016  src = MemOperand(mem.rb(), scratch);
4017  }
4018  lg(dst, src);
4019 }

4021 // Store a "pointer" sized value to the memory location
4022 void MacroAssembler::StoreU64(Register src, const MemOperand& mem,
4023  Register scratch) {
4024  if (!is_int20(mem.offset())) {
4025  DCHECK(scratch != no_reg);
4026  DCHECK(scratch != r0);
4027  mov(scratch, Operand(mem.offset()));
4028  stg(src, MemOperand(mem.rb(), scratch));
4029  } else {
4030  stg(src, mem);
4031  }
4032 }
4033 
4034 // Store a "pointer" sized constant to the memory location
4035 void MacroAssembler::StoreU64(const MemOperand& mem, const Operand& opnd,
4036  Register scratch) {
4037  // Relocations not supported
4038  DCHECK_EQ(opnd.rmode(), RelocInfo::NO_INFO);
4039 
4040  // Try to use MVGHI/MVHI
4041  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(GENERAL_INSTR_EXT) && is_uint12(mem.offset()) &&
4042  mem.getIndexRegister() == r0 && is_int16(opnd.immediate())) {
4043  mvghi(mem, opnd);
4044  } else {
4045  mov(scratch, opnd);
4046  StoreU64(scratch, mem);
4047  }
4048 }

4106 // Variable length depending on whether offset fits into immediate field
4107 // MemOperand of RX or RXY format
4108 void MacroAssembler::LoadU32(Register dst, const MemOperand& mem,
4109  Register scratch) {
4110  Register base = mem.rb();
4111  int offset = mem.offset();
4112 
4113  if (is_int20(offset)) {
4114  llgf(dst, mem);
4115  } else if (scratch != no_reg) {
4116  // Materialize offset into scratch register.
4117  mov(scratch, Operand(offset));
4118  llgf(dst, MemOperand(base, scratch));
4119  } else {
4120  DCHECK(false);
4121  }
4122 }

4257 void MacroAssembler::StoreV128LE(Simd128Register src, const MemOperand& mem,
4258  Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {

4260  is_uint12(mem.offset());
4261  if (use_vstbr) {

4629 // Variable length depending on whether offset fits into immediate field
4630 // MemOperand of RX or RXY format
4631 void MacroAssembler::StoreU32(Register src, const MemOperand& mem,
4632  Register scratch) {
4633  Register base = mem.rb();
4634  int offset = mem.offset();
4635 
4636  bool use_RXform = false;
4637  bool use_RXYform = false;
4638 
4639  if (is_uint12(offset)) {
4640  // RX-format supports unsigned 12-bits offset.
4641  use_RXform = true;
4642  } else if (is_int20(offset)) {
4643  // RXY-format supports signed 20-bits offset.
4644  use_RXYform = true;
4645  } else if (scratch != no_reg) {
4646  // Materialize offset into scratch register.
4647  mov(scratch, Operand(offset));
4648  } else {
4649  // scratch is no_reg
4650  DCHECK(false);
4651  }
4652 
4653  if (use_RXform) {
4654  st(src, mem);
4655  } else if (use_RXYform) {
4656  sty(src, mem);
4657  } else {
4658  StoreU32(src, MemOperand(base, scratch));
4659  }
4660 }

4663  lghr(dst, src);
4664 }

4666 // Loads 16-bits half-word value from memory and sign extends to pointer
4667 // sized register
4668 void MacroAssembler::LoadS16(Register dst, const MemOperand& mem,
4669  Register scratch) {
4670  Register base = mem.rb();
4671  int offset = mem.offset();
4672 
4673  if (!is_int20(offset)) {
4674  DCHECK(scratch != no_reg);
4675  mov(scratch, Operand(offset));
4676  lgh(dst, MemOperand(base, scratch));
4677  } else {
4678  lgh(dst, mem);
4679  }
4680 }

4724 // Shift left logical for 32-bit integer types.
4725 void MacroAssembler::ShiftLeftU32(Register dst, Register src, Register val,
4726  const Operand& val2) {
4727  if (dst == src) {
4728  sll(dst, val, val2);
4729  } else if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(DISTINCT_OPS)) {
4730  sllk(dst, src, val, val2);
4731  } else {
4732  DCHECK(dst != val || val == r0); // The lr/sll path clobbers val.
4733  lr(dst, src);
4734  sll(dst, val, val2);
4735  }
4736 }

4813 // Clear right most # of bits
4814 void MacroAssembler::ClearRightImm(Register dst, Register src,
4815  const Operand& val) {
4816  int numBitsToClear = val.immediate() % (kSystemPointerSize * 8);
4817 
4818  // Try to use RISBG if possible
4819  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(GENERAL_INSTR_EXT)) {
4820  int endBit = 63 - numBitsToClear;
4821  RotateInsertSelectBits(dst, src, Operand::Zero(), Operand(endBit),
4822  Operand::Zero(), true);
4823  return;
4824  }
4825 
4826  uint64_t hexMask = ~((1L << numBitsToClear) - 1);
4827 
4828  // S390 AND instr clobbers source. Make a copy if necessary
4829  if (dst != src) mov(dst, src);
4830 
4831  if (numBitsToClear <= 16) {
4832  nill(dst, Operand(static_cast<uint16_t>(hexMask)));
4833  } else if (numBitsToClear <= 32) {
4834  nilf(dst, Operand(static_cast<uint32_t>(hexMask)));
4835  } else if (numBitsToClear <= 64) {
4836  nilf(dst, Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(0)));
4837  nihf(dst, Operand(hexMask >> 32));
4838  }
4839 }
4840 
4841 void MacroAssembler::Popcnt32(Register dst, Register src) {
4842  DCHECK(src != r0);
4843  DCHECK(dst != r0);
4844 
4845  popcnt(dst, src);
4846  ShiftRightU32(r0, dst, Operand(16));
4847  ar(dst, r0);
4848  ShiftRightU32(r0, dst, Operand(8));
4849  ar(dst, r0);
4850  llgcr(dst, dst);
4851 }
4852 
4853 void MacroAssembler::Popcnt64(Register dst, Register src) {
4854  DCHECK(src != r0);
4855  DCHECK(dst != r0);
4856 
4857  popcnt(dst, src);
4858  ShiftRightU64(r0, dst, Operand(32));
4859  AddS64(dst, r0);
4860  ShiftRightU64(r0, dst, Operand(16));
4861  AddS64(dst, r0);
4862  ShiftRightU64(r0, dst, Operand(8));
4863  AddS64(dst, r0);
4864  LoadU8(dst, dst);
4865 }

4867 void MacroAssembler::SwapP(Register src, Register dst, Register scratch) {
4868  if (src == dst) return;
4869  DCHECK(!AreAliased(src, dst, scratch));
4870  mov(scratch, src);
4871  mov(src, dst);
4872  mov(dst, scratch);
4873 }
4874 
4875 void MacroAssembler::SwapP(Register src, MemOperand dst, Register scratch) {
4876  if (dst.rx() != r0) DCHECK(!AreAliased(src, dst.rx(), scratch));
4877  if (dst.rb() != r0) DCHECK(!AreAliased(src, dst.rb(), scratch));
4878  DCHECK(!AreAliased(src, scratch));
4879  mov(scratch, src);
4880  LoadU64(src, dst);
4881  StoreU64(scratch, dst);
4882 }
4883 
4884 void MacroAssembler::SwapP(MemOperand src, MemOperand dst, Register scratch_0,
4885  Register scratch_1) {
4886  if (src.rx() != r0) DCHECK(!AreAliased(src.rx(), scratch_0, scratch_1));
4887  if (src.rb() != r0) DCHECK(!AreAliased(src.rb(), scratch_0, scratch_1));
4888  if (dst.rx() != r0) DCHECK(!AreAliased(dst.rx(), scratch_0, scratch_1));
4889  if (dst.rb() != r0) DCHECK(!AreAliased(dst.rb(), scratch_0, scratch_1));
4890  DCHECK(!AreAliased(scratch_0, scratch_1));
4891  LoadU64(scratch_0, src);
4892  LoadU64(scratch_1, dst);
4893  StoreU64(scratch_0, dst);
4894  StoreU64(scratch_1, src);
4895 }
4896 
4897 void MacroAssembler::SwapFloat32(DoubleRegister src, DoubleRegister dst,
4898  DoubleRegister scratch) {
4899  if (src == dst) return;
4900  DCHECK(!AreAliased(src, dst, scratch));
4901  ldr(scratch, src);
4902  ldr(src, dst);
4903  ldr(dst, scratch);
4904 }

4914 void MacroAssembler::SwapFloat32(MemOperand src, MemOperand dst,
4915  DoubleRegister scratch) {

4921  StoreF32(scratch, dst);
4922  StoreF32(d0, src);
4923  // restore d0
4924  LoadF64(d0, MemOperand(sp));
4925  lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, kDoubleSize));
4926 }

5009 void MacroAssembler::LoadEntryFromBuiltinIndex(Register builtin_index,
5010  Register target) {
5011  static_assert(kSystemPointerSize == 8);
5012  static_assert(kSmiTagSize == 1);
5013  static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
5014  // The builtin_index register contains the builtin index as a Smi.
5015  if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
5016  ShiftRightS64(target, builtin_index,
5017  Operand(kSmiShift - kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
5018  } else {
5019  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
5020  ShiftLeftU64(target, builtin_index,
5021  Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2 - kSmiShift));
5022  }
5023  LoadU64(target, MemOperand(kRootRegister, target,
5024  IsolateData::builtin_entry_table_offset()));
5025 }

5048 void MacroAssembler::LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(Register destination,
5049  Register dispatch_handle,
5050  Register scratch) {
5051  DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, dispatch_handle, scratch));
5052  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5053 
5054  Register index = destination;
5055  CHECK(root_array_available());
5056  LoadU64(scratch,
5057  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kJSDispatchTable));
5058  ShiftRightU64(index, dispatch_handle, Operand(kJSDispatchHandleShift));
5059  ShiftLeftU64(index, index, Operand(kJSDispatchTableEntrySizeLog2));
5060  AddS64(scratch, scratch, index);
5061  LoadU64(destination, MemOperand(scratch, JSDispatchEntry::kEntrypointOffset));
5062 }

5064 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING

5087 void MacroAssembler::CallJSFunction(Register function_object,
5088  uint16_t argument_count) {
5089  Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
5090 #if V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5091  Register dispatch_handle = r0;
5092  Register scratch = ip;
5093  LoadU32(dispatch_handle,
5094  FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
5095  LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(code, dispatch_handle, scratch);
5096  Call(code);
5097 #else
5098  LoadTaggedField(code,
5099  FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
5100  CallCodeObject(code);
5101 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5102 }
5103 
5104 #if V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5105 void MacroAssembler::CallJSDispatchEntry(JSDispatchHandle dispatch_handle,
5106  uint16_t argument_count) {
5107  Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
5108  Register dispatch_handle_reg = r0;
5109  Register scratch = ip;
5110  mov(dispatch_handle_reg,
5111  Operand(dispatch_handle.value(), RelocInfo::JS_DISPATCH_HANDLE));
5112  // WARNING: This entrypoint load is only safe because we are storing a
5113  // RelocInfo for the dispatch handle in the movl above (thus keeping the
5114  // dispatch entry alive) _and_ because the entrypoints are not compactable
5115  // (thus meaning that the calculation in the entrypoint load is not
5116  // invalidated by a compaction).
5117  // TODO(leszeks): Make this less of a footgun.
5118  static_assert(!JSDispatchTable::kSupportsCompaction);
5119  LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(code, dispatch_handle_reg, scratch);
5120  CHECK_EQ(argument_count,
5121  IsolateGroup::current()->js_dispatch_table()->GetParameterCount(
5122  dispatch_handle));
5123  Call(code);
5124 }
5125 #endif

5137 #else

5141 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5142 }

5144 #if V8_OS_ZOS
5145 // Helper for CallApiFunctionAndReturn().
5146 void MacroAssembler::zosStoreReturnAddressAndCall(Register target,
5147  Register scratch) {
5148  DCHECK(target == r3 || target == r4);
5149  // Shuffle the arguments from Linux arg register to XPLINK arg regs
5150  mov(r1, r2);
5151  if (target == r3) {
5152  mov(r2, r3);
5153  } else {
5154  mov(r2, r3);
5155  mov(r3, r4);
5156  }
5157 
5158  // Update System Stack Pointer with the appropriate XPLINK stack bias.
5159  lay(r4, MemOperand(sp, -kStackPointerBias));
5160 
5161  // Preserve r7 by placing into callee-saved register r13
5162  mov(r13, r7);
5163 
5164  // Load function pointer from slot 1 of fn desc.
5165  LoadU64(ip, MemOperand(scratch, kSystemPointerSize));
5166  // Load environment from slot 0 of fn desc.
5167  LoadU64(r5, MemOperand(scratch));
5168 
5169  StoreReturnAddressAndCall(ip);
5170 
5171  // Restore r7 from r13
5172  mov(r7, r13);
5173 }
5174 #endif // V8_OS_ZOS

5176 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5177 
5178 void MacroAssembler::ResolveWasmCodePointer(Register target) {
5179  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5180  static_assert(!V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL);
5181  ExternalReference global_jump_table =
5182  ExternalReference::wasm_code_pointer_table();
5183  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5184  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5185  Move(scratch, global_jump_table);
5186  static_assert(sizeof(wasm::WasmCodePointerTableEntry) == kSystemPointerSize);
5187  ShiftLeftU32(target, target, Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
5188  LoadU64(target, MemOperand(scratch, target));
5189 }
5190 
5191 void MacroAssembler::CallWasmCodePointer(Register target,
5192  CallJumpMode call_jump_mode) {
5193  ResolveWasmCodePointer(target);
5194  if (call_jump_mode == CallJumpMode::kTailCall) {
5195  Jump(target);
5196  } else {
5197  Call(target);
5198  }
5199 }

5207 
5208 void MacroAssembler::StoreReturnAddressAndCall(Register target) {
5209  // This generates the final instruction sequence for calls to C functions
5210  // once an exit frame has been constructed.
5211  //
5212  // Note that this assumes the caller code (i.e. the InstructionStream object
5213  // currently being generated) is immovable or that the callee function cannot
5214  // trigger GC, since the callee function will return to it.
5215 
5216 #if V8_OS_ZOS
5217  Register ra = r7;
5218 #else
5219  Register ra = r14;
5220 #endif
5221  Label return_label;
5222  larl(ra, &return_label); // Generate the return addr of call later.
5223 #if V8_OS_ZOS
5224  // Mimic the XPLINK expected no-op (2-byte) instruction at the return point.
5225  // When the C call returns, the 2 bytes are skipped and then the proper
5226  // instruction is executed.
5227  lay(ra, MemOperand(ra, -2));
5228 #endif
5229  StoreU64(ra, MemOperand(sp, kStackFrameRASlot * kSystemPointerSize));
5230 
5231  // zLinux ABI requires caller's frame to have sufficient space for callee
5232  // preserved regsiter save area.
5233  b(target);
5234  bind(&return_label);
5235 }
5236 
5237 // Check if the code object is marked for deoptimization. If it is, then it
5238 // jumps to the CompileLazyDeoptimizedCode builtin. In order to do this we need
5239 // to:
5240 // 1. read from memory the word that contains that bit, which can be found in
5241 // the flags in the referenced {Code} object;
5242 // 2. test kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit in those flags; and
5243 // 3. if it is not zero then it jumps to the builtin.
5244 //
5245 // Note: With leaptiering we simply assert the code is not deoptimized.
5246 void MacroAssembler::BailoutIfDeoptimized(Register scratch) {
5247  int offset = InstructionStream::kCodeOffset - InstructionStream::kHeaderSize;
5248  if (v8_flags.debug_code || !V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL) {
5249  LoadTaggedField(scratch,
5250  MemOperand(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister, offset));
5251  TestCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(scratch, scratch);
5252  }
5253 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5254  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
5255  Assert(to_condition(kZero), AbortReason::kInvalidDeoptimizedCode);
5256  }
5257 #else
5258  Jump(BUILTIN_CODE(isolate(), CompileLazyDeoptimizedCode),
5259  RelocInfo::CODE_TARGET, ne);
5260 #endif
5261 }
5262 
5263 void MacroAssembler::CallForDeoptimization(Builtin target, int, Label* exit,
5264  DeoptimizeKind kind, Label* ret,
5265  Label*) {
5266  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5267  LoadU64(ip, MemOperand(kRootRegister,
5268  IsolateData::BuiltinEntrySlotOffset(target)));
5269  Call(ip);
5270  DCHECK_EQ(SizeOfCodeGeneratedSince(exit),
5271  (kind == DeoptimizeKind::kLazy) ? Deoptimizer::kLazyDeoptExitSize
5272  : Deoptimizer::kEagerDeoptExitSize);
5273 }

5286 void MacroAssembler::CountLeadingZerosU64(Register dst, Register src,

5289  clzg(dst, src);

5297 void MacroAssembler::CountTrailingZerosU32(Register dst, Register src,
5298  Register scratch_pair) {
5299  Register scratch0 = scratch_pair;
5300  Register scratch1 = Register::from_code(scratch_pair.code() + 1);
5301  DCHECK(!AreAliased(dst, scratch0, scratch1));
5302  DCHECK(!AreAliased(src, scratch0, scratch1));
5303 
5304  Label done;
5305  // Check if src is all zeros.
5306  ltr(scratch1, src);
5307  mov(dst, Operand(32));
5308  beq(&done);
5309  llgfr(scratch1, scratch1);
5310  lcgr(scratch0, scratch1);
5311  ngr(scratch1, scratch0);
5312  flogr(scratch0, scratch1);
5313  mov(dst, Operand(63));
5314  SubS64(dst, scratch0);
5315  bind(&done);
5316 }
5317 
5318 void MacroAssembler::CountTrailingZerosU64(Register dst, Register src,
5319  Register scratch_pair) {
5320  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(MISC_INSTR_EXT4)) {
5321  ctzg(dst, src);
5322  } else {
5323  Register scratch0 = scratch_pair;
5324  Register scratch1 = Register::from_code(scratch_pair.code() + 1);
5325  DCHECK(!AreAliased(dst, scratch0, scratch1));
5326  DCHECK(!AreAliased(src, scratch0, scratch1));
5327 
5328  Label done;
5329  // Check if src is all zeros.
5330  ltgr(scratch1, src);
5331  mov(dst, Operand(64));
5332  beq(&done);
5333  lcgr(scratch0, scratch1);
5334  ngr(scratch0, scratch1);
5335  flogr(scratch0, scratch0);
5336  mov(dst, Operand(63));
5337  SubS64(dst, scratch0);
5338  bind(&done);
5339  }
5340 }
5341 
5342 void MacroAssembler::AtomicCmpExchangeHelper(Register addr, Register output,
5343  Register old_value,
5344  Register new_value, int start,
5345  int end, int shift_amount,
5346  int offset, Register temp0,
5347  Register temp1) {
5348  LoadU32(temp0, MemOperand(addr, offset));
5349  llgfr(temp1, temp0);
5350  RotateInsertSelectBits(temp0, old_value, Operand(start), Operand(end),
5351  Operand(shift_amount), false);
5352  RotateInsertSelectBits(temp1, new_value, Operand(start), Operand(end),
5353  Operand(shift_amount), false);
5354  CmpAndSwap(temp0, temp1, MemOperand(addr, offset));
5355  RotateInsertSelectBits(output, temp0, Operand(start + shift_amount),
5356  Operand(end + shift_amount),
5357  Operand(64 - shift_amount), true);
5358 }
5359 
5360 void MacroAssembler::AtomicCmpExchangeU8(Register addr, Register output,
5361  Register old_value, Register new_value,
5362  Register temp0, Register temp1) {
5363 #ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
5364 #define ATOMIC_COMP_EXCHANGE_BYTE(i) \
5365  { \
5366  constexpr int idx = (i); \
5367  static_assert(idx <= 3 && idx >= 0, "idx is out of range!"); \
5368  constexpr int start = 32 + 8 * idx; \
5369  constexpr int end = start + 7; \
5370  constexpr int shift_amount = (3 - idx) * 8; \
5371  AtomicCmpExchangeHelper(addr, output, old_value, new_value, start, end, \
5372  shift_amount, -idx, temp0, temp1); \
5373  }
5374 #else
5375 #define ATOMIC_COMP_EXCHANGE_BYTE(i) \
5376  { \
5377  constexpr int idx = (i); \
5378  static_assert(idx <= 3 && idx >= 0, "idx is out of range!"); \
5379  constexpr int start = 32 + 8 * (3 - idx); \
5380  constexpr int end = start + 7; \
5381  constexpr int shift_amount = idx * 8; \
5382  AtomicCmpExchangeHelper(addr, output, old_value, new_value, start, end, \
5383  shift_amount, -idx, temp0, temp1); \
5384  }
5385 #endif
5386 
5387  Label one, two, three, done;
5388  tmll(addr, Operand(3));
5389  b(Condition(1), &three);
5390  b(Condition(2), &two);
5391  b(Condition(4), &one);
5392  /* ending with 0b00 */
5393  ATOMIC_COMP_EXCHANGE_BYTE(0);
5394  b(&done);
5395  /* ending with 0b01 */
5396  bind(&one);
5397  ATOMIC_COMP_EXCHANGE_BYTE(1);
5398  b(&done);
5399  /* ending with 0b10 */
5400  bind(&two);
5401  ATOMIC_COMP_EXCHANGE_BYTE(2);
5402  b(&done);
5403  /* ending with 0b11 */
5404  bind(&three);
5405  ATOMIC_COMP_EXCHANGE_BYTE(3);
5406  bind(&done);
5407 }
5408 
5409 void MacroAssembler::AtomicCmpExchangeU16(Register addr, Register output,
5410  Register old_value,
5411  Register new_value, Register temp0,
5412  Register temp1) {
5413 #ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
5414 #define ATOMIC_COMP_EXCHANGE_HALFWORD(i) \
5415  { \
5416  constexpr int idx = (i); \
5417  static_assert(idx <= 1 && idx >= 0, "idx is out of range!"); \
5418  constexpr int start = 32 + 16 * idx; \
5419  constexpr int end = start + 15; \
5420  constexpr int shift_amount = (1 - idx) * 16; \
5421  AtomicCmpExchangeHelper(addr, output, old_value, new_value, start, end, \
5422  shift_amount, -idx * 2, temp0, temp1); \
5423  }
5424 #else
5425 #define ATOMIC_COMP_EXCHANGE_HALFWORD(i) \
5426  { \
5427  constexpr int idx = (i); \
5428  static_assert(idx <= 1 && idx >= 0, "idx is out of range!"); \
5429  constexpr int start = 32 + 16 * (1 - idx); \
5430  constexpr int end = start + 15; \
5431  constexpr int shift_amount = idx * 16; \
5432  AtomicCmpExchangeHelper(addr, output, old_value, new_value, start, end, \
5433  shift_amount, -idx * 2, temp0, temp1); \
5434  }
5435 #endif
5436 
5437  Label two, done;
5438  tmll(addr, Operand(3));
5439  b(Condition(2), &two);
5440  ATOMIC_COMP_EXCHANGE_HALFWORD(0);
5441  b(&done);
5442  bind(&two);
5443  ATOMIC_COMP_EXCHANGE_HALFWORD(1);
5444  bind(&done);
5445 }
5446 
5447 void MacroAssembler::AtomicExchangeHelper(Register addr, Register value,
5448  Register output, int start, int end,
5449  int shift_amount, int offset,
5450  Register scratch) {
5451  Label do_cs;
5452  LoadU32(output, MemOperand(addr, offset));
5453  bind(&do_cs);
5454  llgfr(scratch, output);
5455  RotateInsertSelectBits(scratch, value, Operand(start), Operand(end),
5456  Operand(shift_amount), false);
5457  csy(output, scratch, MemOperand(addr, offset));
5458  bne(&do_cs, Label::kNear);
5459  srl(output, Operand(shift_amount));
5460 }
5461 
5462 void MacroAssembler::AtomicExchangeU8(Register addr, Register value,
5463  Register output, Register scratch) {
5464 #ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
5465 #define ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_BYTE(i) \
5466  { \
5467  constexpr int idx = (i); \
5468  static_assert(idx <= 3 && idx >= 0, "idx is out of range!"); \
5469  constexpr int start = 32 + 8 * idx; \
5470  constexpr int end = start + 7; \
5471  constexpr int shift_amount = (3 - idx) * 8; \
5472  AtomicExchangeHelper(addr, value, output, start, end, shift_amount, -idx, \
5473  scratch); \
5474  }
5475 #else
5476 #define ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_BYTE(i) \
5477  { \
5478  constexpr int idx = (i); \
5479  static_assert(idx <= 3 && idx >= 0, "idx is out of range!"); \
5480  constexpr int start = 32 + 8 * (3 - idx); \
5481  constexpr int end = start + 7; \
5482  constexpr int shift_amount = idx * 8; \
5483  AtomicExchangeHelper(addr, value, output, start, end, shift_amount, -idx, \
5484  scratch); \
5485  }
5486 #endif
5487  Label three, two, one, done;
5488  tmll(addr, Operand(3));
5489  b(Condition(1), &three);
5490  b(Condition(2), &two);
5491  b(Condition(4), &one);
5492 
5493  // end with 0b00
5494  ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_BYTE(0);
5495  b(&done);
5496 
5497  // ending with 0b01
5498  bind(&one);
5499  ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_BYTE(1);
5500  b(&done);
5501 
5502  // ending with 0b10
5503  bind(&two);
5504  ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_BYTE(2);
5505  b(&done);
5506 
5507  // ending with 0b11
5508  bind(&three);
5509  ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_BYTE(3);
5510 
5511  bind(&done);
5512 }
5513 
5514 void MacroAssembler::AtomicExchangeU16(Register addr, Register value,
5515  Register output, Register scratch) {
5516 #ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
5517 #define ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_HALFWORD(i) \
5518  { \
5519  constexpr int idx = (i); \
5520  static_assert(idx <= 1 && idx >= 0, "idx is out of range!"); \
5521  constexpr int start = 32 + 16 * idx; \
5522  constexpr int end = start + 15; \
5523  constexpr int shift_amount = (1 - idx) * 16; \
5524  AtomicExchangeHelper(addr, value, output, start, end, shift_amount, \
5525  -idx * 2, scratch); \
5526  }
5527 #else
5528 #define ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_HALFWORD(i) \
5529  { \
5530  constexpr int idx = (i); \
5531  static_assert(idx <= 1 && idx >= 0, "idx is out of range!"); \
5532  constexpr int start = 32 + 16 * (1 - idx); \
5533  constexpr int end = start + 15; \
5534  constexpr int shift_amount = idx * 16; \
5535  AtomicExchangeHelper(addr, value, output, start, end, shift_amount, \
5536  -idx * 2, scratch); \
5537  }
5538 #endif
5539  Label two, done;
5540  tmll(addr, Operand(3));
5541  b(Condition(2), &two);
5542 
5543  // end with 0b00
5544  ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_HALFWORD(0);
5545  b(&done);
5546 
5547  // ending with 0b10
5548  bind(&two);
5549  ATOMIC_EXCHANGE_HALFWORD(1);
5550 
5551  bind(&done);
5552 }

5916  Simd128Register src2, Register scratch1,
5917  Register scratch2, Register scratch3) {
5918  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(VECTOR_ENHANCE_FACILITY_3)) {
5919  vml(dst, src1, src2, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(3));
5920  } else {
5921  Register scratch_1 = scratch1;
5922  Register scratch_2 = scratch2;
5923  for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
5924  vlgv(scratch_1, src1, MemOperand(r0, i), Condition(3));
5925  vlgv(scratch_2, src2, MemOperand(r0, i), Condition(3));
5926  MulS64(scratch_1, scratch_2);
5927  scratch_1 = scratch2;
5928  scratch_2 = scratch3;
5929  }
5930  vlvgp(dst, scratch1, scratch2);
5931  }
5932 }

6199  DCHECK(dst != src1 && dst != src2); \

6201  extract_high(scratch2, src2, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(mode)); \

6203  Condition(mode + 1)); \
6204  extract_low(scratch1, src1, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(mode)); \
6205  extract_low(scratch2, src2, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(mode)); \
6206  op(scratch1, scratch1, scratch2, Condition(0), Condition(0), \
6207  Condition(mode + 1));

6391 void MacroAssembler::I8x16Swizzle(Simd128Register dst, Simd128Register src1,
6392  Simd128Register src2, Register scratch1,
6393  Register scratch2, Simd128Register scratch3) {
6394  DCHECK(!AreAliased(src1, scratch3));
6395  DCHECK(!AreAliased(src2, scratch3));
6396  // Saturate the indices to 5 bits. Input indices more than 31 should
6397  // return 0.
6398  vrepi(scratch3, Operand(31), Condition(0));
6399  vmnl(scratch3, src2, scratch3, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(0));
6400  // Input needs to be reversed.
6401  vlgv(scratch1, src1, MemOperand(r0, 0), Condition(3));
6402  vlgv(scratch2, src1, MemOperand(r0, 1), Condition(3));
6403  lrvgr(scratch1, scratch1);
6404  lrvgr(scratch2, scratch2);
6405  vlvgp(dst, scratch2, scratch1);
6406  vx(kDoubleRegZero, kDoubleRegZero, kDoubleRegZero, Condition(0), Condition(0),
6407  Condition(0));
6408  vperm(dst, dst, kDoubleRegZero, scratch3, Condition(0), Condition(0));
6409 }

6429 void MacroAssembler::I32x4DotI8x16AddS(
6430  Simd128Register dst, Simd128Register src1, Simd128Register src2,
6431  Simd128Register src3, Simd128Register scratch1, Simd128Register scratch2) {

6440  vmo(dst, dst, scratch2, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(1));
6441  va(dst, scratch1, dst, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(2));
6442  // Add src3.
6443  va(dst, dst, src3, Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(2));

6598 void MacroAssembler::LoadStackLimit(Register destination, StackLimitKind kind) {
6599  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6600  DCHECK(root_array_available());
6601  intptr_t offset = kind == StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit
6602  ? IsolateData::real_jslimit_offset()
6603  : IsolateData::jslimit_offset();

6608 void MacroAssembler::Switch(Register scratch, Register value,
6609  int case_value_base, Label** labels,
6610  int num_labels) {
6611  Label fallthrough, jump_table;
6612  if (case_value_base != 0) {
6613  SubS64(value, value, Operand(case_value_base));
6614  }
6615  CmpU64(value, Operand(num_labels));
6616  bge(&fallthrough);
6617 
6618  int entry_size_log2 = 3;
6619  ShiftLeftU32(value, value, Operand(entry_size_log2));
6620  larl(r1, &jump_table);
6621  lay(r1, MemOperand(value, r1));
6622  b(r1);
6623 
6624  bind(&jump_table);
6625  for (int i = 0; i < num_labels; ++i) {
6626  b(labels[i]);
6627  dh(0);
6628  }
6629  bind(&fallthrough);
6630 }

6638 void MacroAssembler::JumpIfCodeIsTurbofanned(Register code, Register scratch,
6639  Label* if_turbofanned) {
6640  LoadU32(scratch, FieldMemOperand(code, Code::kFlagsOffset));
6641  TestBit(scratch, Code::kIsTurbofannedBit, scratch);
6642  bne(if_turbofanned);

6645 void MacroAssembler::TryLoadOptimizedOsrCode(Register scratch_and_result,
6646  CodeKind min_opt_level,
6647  Register feedback_vector,
6648  FeedbackSlot slot,
6649  Label* on_result,
6650  Label::Distance) {
6651  Label fallthrough, clear_slot;
6652  LoadTaggedField(
6653  scratch_and_result,
6654  FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector,
6655  FeedbackVector::OffsetOfElementAt(slot.ToInt())));
6656  LoadWeakValue(scratch_and_result, scratch_and_result, &fallthrough);
6657 
6658  // Is it marked_for_deoptimization? If yes, clear the slot.
6659  {
6660  // The entry references a CodeWrapper object. Unwrap it now.
6661  LoadTaggedField(
6662  scratch_and_result,
6663  FieldMemOperand(scratch_and_result, CodeWrapper::kCodeOffset));
6664 
6665  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6666  Register temp = temps.Acquire();
6667  JumpIfCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(scratch_and_result, temp, &clear_slot);
6668  if (min_opt_level == CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS) {
6669  JumpIfCodeIsTurbofanned(scratch_and_result, temp, on_result);
6670  b(&fallthrough);
6671  } else {
6672  b(on_result);
6673  }
6674  }
6675 
6676  bind(&clear_slot);
6677  mov(scratch_and_result, ClearedValue());
6678  StoreTaggedField(
6679  scratch_and_result,
6680  FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector,
6681  FeedbackVector::OffsetOfElementAt(slot.ToInt())));
6682 
6683  bind(&fallthrough);
6684  mov(scratch_and_result, Operand::Zero());
6685 }
6686 
6687 // Calls an API function. Allocates HandleScope, extracts returned value
6688 // from handle and propagates exceptions. Clobbers C argument registers
6689 // and C caller-saved registers. Restores context. On return removes
6690 // (*argc_operand + slots_to_drop_on_return) * kSystemPointerSize
6691 // (GCed, includes the call JS arguments space and the additional space
6692 // allocated for the fast call).
6693 void CallApiFunctionAndReturn(MacroAssembler* masm, bool with_profiling,
6694  Register function_address,
6695  ExternalReference thunk_ref, Register thunk_arg,
6696  int slots_to_drop_on_return,
6697  MemOperand* argc_operand,
6698  MemOperand return_value_operand) {
6699  using ER = ExternalReference;
6700 
6701  Isolate* isolate = masm->isolate();
6702  MemOperand next_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6703  ER::handle_scope_next_address(isolate), no_reg);
6704  MemOperand limit_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6705  ER::handle_scope_limit_address(isolate), no_reg);
6706  MemOperand level_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6707  ER::handle_scope_level_address(isolate), no_reg);
6708 
6709  Register return_value = r2;
6710 #if V8_OS_ZOS
6711  Register scratch = r6;
6712 #else
6713  Register scratch = ip;
6714 #endif
6715  Register scratch2 = r1;
6716 
6717  // Allocate HandleScope in callee-saved registers.
6718  // We will need to restore the HandleScope after the call to the API function,
6719  // by allocating it in callee-saved registers it'll be preserved by C code.
6720 #if V8_OS_ZOS
6721  Register prev_next_address_reg = r14;
6722 #else
6723  Register prev_next_address_reg = r6;
6724 #endif
6725  Register prev_limit_reg = r7;
6726  Register prev_level_reg = r8;
6727 
6728  // C arguments (kCArgRegs[0/1]) are expected to be initialized outside, so
6729  // this function must not corrupt them (return_value overlaps with
6730  // kCArgRegs[0] but that's ok because we start using it only after the C
6731  // call).
6732  DCHECK(!AreAliased(kCArgRegs[0], kCArgRegs[1], // C args
6733  scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
6734  // function_address and thunk_arg might overlap but this function must not
6735  // corrupted them until the call is made (i.e. overlap with return_value is
6736  // fine).
6737  DCHECK(!AreAliased(function_address, // incoming parameters
6738  scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
6739  DCHECK(!AreAliased(thunk_arg, // incoming parameters
6740  scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
6741  {
6742  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
6743  "Allocate HandleScope in callee-save registers.");
6744  __ LoadU64(prev_next_address_reg, next_mem_op);
6745  __ LoadU64(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
6746  __ LoadU32(prev_level_reg, level_mem_op);
6747  __ AddS64(scratch, prev_level_reg, Operand(1));
6748  __ StoreU32(scratch, level_mem_op);
6749  }
6750 
6751  Label profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, done_api_call;
6752  if (with_profiling) {
6753  __ RecordComment("Check if profiler or side effects check is enabled");
6754  __ LoadU8(scratch,
6755  __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kExecutionMode));
6756  __ CmpS64(scratch, Operand::Zero());
6757  __ bne(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, Label::kNear);
6758 #ifdef V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
6759  __ RecordComment("Check if RCS is enabled");
6760  __ Move(scratch, ER::address_of_runtime_stats_flag());
6761  __ LoadU32(scratch, MemOperand(scratch, 0));
6762  __ CmpS64(scratch, Operand::Zero());
6763  __ bne(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, Label::kNear);
6764 #endif // V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
6765  }
6766 
6767  __ RecordComment("Call the api function directly.");
6768 #if V8_OS_ZOS
6769  __ mov(scratch, function_address);
6770  __ zosStoreReturnAddressAndCall(function_address, scratch);
6771 #else
6772  __ StoreReturnAddressAndCall(function_address);
6773 #endif
6774  __ bind(&done_api_call);
6775 
6776  Label propagate_exception;
6777  Label delete_allocated_handles;
6778  Label leave_exit_frame;
6779 
6780  __ RecordComment("Load the value from ReturnValue");
6781  __ LoadU64(r2, return_value_operand);
6782 
6783  {
6784  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
6785  masm,
6786  "No more valid handles (the result handle was the last one)."
6787  "Restore previous handle scope.");
6788  __ StoreU64(prev_next_address_reg, next_mem_op);
6789  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6790  __ LoadU32(scratch, level_mem_op);
6791  __ SubS64(scratch, Operand(1));
6792  __ CmpS64(scratch, prev_level_reg);
6793  __ Check(eq, AbortReason::kUnexpectedLevelAfterReturnFromApiCall);
6794  }
6795  __ StoreU32(prev_level_reg, level_mem_op);
6796  __ CmpS64(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
6797  __ bne(&delete_allocated_handles, Label::kNear);
6798  }
6799 
6800  __ RecordComment("Leave the API exit frame.");
6801  __ bind(&leave_exit_frame);
6802  Register argc_reg = prev_limit_reg;
6803  if (argc_operand != nullptr) {
6804  // Load the number of stack slots to drop before LeaveExitFrame modifies sp.
6805  __ LoadU64(argc_reg, *argc_operand);
6806  }
6807  __ LeaveExitFrame(scratch);
6808 
6809  // Check if the function scheduled an exception.
6810  {
6811  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
6812  "Check if the function scheduled an exception.");
6813  __ LoadU64(scratch2, __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6814  ER::exception_address(isolate), no_reg));
6815  __ CompareRoot(scratch2, RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
6816  __ bne(&propagate_exception, Label::kNear);
6817  }
6818 
6819  __ AssertJSAny(return_value, scratch, scratch2,
6820  AbortReason::kAPICallReturnedInvalidObject);
6821 
6822  if (argc_operand == nullptr) {
6823  DCHECK_NE(slots_to_drop_on_return, 0);
6824  __ AddS64(sp, sp, Operand(slots_to_drop_on_return * kSystemPointerSize));
6825 
6826  } else {
6827  // {argc_operand} was loaded into {argc_reg} above.
6828  __ AddS64(sp, sp, Operand(slots_to_drop_on_return * kSystemPointerSize));
6829  __ ShiftLeftU64(r0, argc_reg, Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
6830  __ AddS64(sp, sp, r0);
6831  }
6832 
6833  __ b(r14);
6834 
6835  if (with_profiling) {
6836  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "Call the api function via thunk wrapper.");
6837  __ bind(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled);
6838  // Additional parameter is the address of the actual callback function.
6839  if (thunk_arg.is_valid()) {
6840  MemOperand thunk_arg_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
6841  IsolateFieldId::kApiCallbackThunkArgument);
6842  __ StoreU64(thunk_arg, thunk_arg_mem_op);
6843  }
6844  __ Move(scratch, thunk_ref);
6845 #if V8_OS_ZOS
6846  __ zosStoreReturnAddressAndCall(function_address, scratch);
6847 #else
6848  __ StoreReturnAddressAndCall(scratch);
6849 #endif
6850  __ b(&done_api_call);
6851  }
6852 
6853  __ RecordComment("An exception was thrown. Propagate it.");
6854  __ bind(&propagate_exception);
6855  __ TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kPropagateException);
6856 
6857  // HandleScope limit has changed. Delete allocated extensions.
6858  {
6859  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
6860  masm, "HandleScope limit has changed. Delete allocated extensions.");
6861  __ bind(&delete_allocated_handles);
6862  __ StoreU64(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
6863  // Save the return value in a callee-save register.
6864  Register saved_result = prev_limit_reg;
6865  __ mov(saved_result, return_value);
6866  __ PrepareCallCFunction(1, scratch);
6867  __ Move(kCArgRegs[0], ER::isolate_address());
6868  __ CallCFunction(ER::delete_handle_scope_extensions(), 1);
6869  __ mov(return_value, saved_result);
6870  __ b(&leave_exit_frame, Label::kNear);
6871  }
6872 }
6873
